%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Findian-overseas-bank-q2-results-net-profit-rises-25-to-rs-627-crore-123102700622_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Caleb%20Hammer%20promised%20to%20save%20them%20from%20financial%20ruin%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20seems%20to%20actually%20be%20working%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Caleb%20Hammer%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651be46a617692f0d03d4f78%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECaleb%20Hammer%2FYouTube%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ECaleb%20Hammer%20has%20become%20a%20fixture%20on%20finance%20TikTok.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20ruthlessly%20goes%20through%20his%20guests'%20finances%20hoping%20to%20drive%20change%20%E2%80%94%20three%20spoke%20to%20Insider%20about%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhile%20it%20could%20feel%20chaotic%20and%20uncomfortable%2C%20they%20generally%20said%20it%20spurred%20lasting%20change.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDuncan%20Bell%20was%20in%20a%20really%20bad%20spot%20when%20he%20appeared%20on%20Caleb%20Hammer's%20financial%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20%2457%2C000%20in%20debt%2C%20and%20the%20minimum%20monthly%20payments%20were%20eating%20up%20a%20good%20chunk%20of%20his%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20felt%20like%20there%20was%20no%20way%20to%20dig%20himself%20out%20%E2%80%94%20he%20had%20a%20low-paid%20job%20delivering%20cookies%2C%20and%20his%20hours%20kept%20getting%20cut%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20also%20been%20struggling%20with%20his%20diagnosis%20of%20bipolar%202%20disorder%2C%20which%20led%20him%20to%20bad%20decisions%20and%20a%20debt%20spiral.%20He%20had%20just%20started%20medication%20which%20had%20curbed%20his%20spending%20habits%20and%20made%20him%20realize%20how%20bad%20his%20situation%20had%20become.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBell%2C%20who's%2026%20and%20lives%20in%20San%20Antonio%2C%20said%20reality%20was%20creeping%20up%20on%20him%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20until%20he%20was%20in%20front%20of%20Hammer%20on%20%26quot%3BFinancial%20Audit%26quot%3B%20that%20it%20really%20hit%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20Hammer's%20bread%20and%20butter.%20In%20multiple%20interviews%20per%20week%2C%20he%20invites%20a%20guest%20on%20and%20rifles%20through%20their%20bank%20accounts%2C%20credit%20cards%2C%20and%20debts%20in%20excruciating%20detail%2C%20making%20them%20face%20their%20finances%20directly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20does%20it%20all%20with%20a%20heavy%20dose%20of%20tough%20love%2C%20pounding%20away%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fcaleb-hammer-best-debt-budget-advice-youtube-finance-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20advice%20to%20cut%20overspending%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20often%20getting%20pretty%20annoyed%20in%20the%20process%20(he%20regularly%20tells%20his%20guests%20he's%20angry%20at%20the%20debt%2C%20%26quot%3Bnot%20at%20you.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20spoke%20to%20three%20previous%20guests%20to%20see%20how%20they%20fared%20after%20going%20on%20the%20show.%20Hammer%20himself%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20to%20be%20interviewed%20for%20this%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFacing%20their%20finances%20head%20on%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBell%20appeared%20on%20the%20show%20in%20May.%20He%20told%20Hammer%20he%20was%20bringing%20in%20%242%2C150%20per%20month%2C%20a%20figure%20that%20could%20shrink%20with%20his%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%2C%20he%20recalled%20to%20Insider%2C%20he%20broke%20down%20in%20tears.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHammer%2C%20who%20praised%20Bell%20for%20being%20so%20open%2C%20suggested%20an%20aggressive%20budget%20to%20tackle%20the%20debt%2C%20and%20also%20told%20him%20he%20needed%20to%20make%20%26quot%3Bmuch%2C%20much%2C%20much%2C%20much%20more%20money%26quot%3B%20to%20dig%20himself%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBell%20took%20his%20advice.%20In%20the%20four%20months%20since%2C%20has%20got%20a%20customer-service%20job%20at%20General%20Electric%20that's%20much%20more%20secure%2C%20and%20comes%20with%20opportunities%20for%20overtime%20and%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20also%20committed%20to%20home%20cooking%20instead%20of%20getting%20fast%20food%2C%20and%20controlling%20his%20budget.%20He%20sold%20his%20car%2C%20shaving%20%2417%2C000%20from%20his%20debt%20in%20one%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20actually%20just%20genuinely%20happy%20at%20this%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBell%20said%20he%20benefitted%20from%20Hammer's%20direct%20advice%20because%20he%20was%20open%20to%20it.%20He's%20watched%20a%20few%20other%20episodes%20where%20people%20make%20excuses%20or%20get%20defensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20straight%20up%20didn't%20deny%20my%20own%20faults%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20just%20like%2C%20yeah%2C%20I'm%20really%20making%20stupid%20decisions%20here.%20I%20just%20need%20some%20help.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBell%20said%20he%20despairs%20watching%20some%20guests%20racking%20up%20enormous%20debt%20(with%2C%20as%20Hammer%20would%20say%2C%20%26quot%3Bdeath%26quot%3B%20interest%20rates)%20so%20they%20can%20buy%20a%20fancy%20car.%20Others%20reject%20jobs%20they%20think%20are%20beneath%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHammer%20has%20been%20doing%20%26quot%3BFinancial%20Audit%26quot%3B%20for%20around%20a%20year%2C%20and%20is%20starting%20to%20invite%20guests%20back.%20In%20one%20posted%20last%20month%2C%20a%2023-year-old%20Twitch%20streamer%20named%20Adrianah%20Lee%20returned%20to%20the%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Lee's%20original%20episode%20she%20was%20avoiding%20paying%20her%20taxes%2C%20had%20racked%20up%20tens%20of%20thousands%20on%20maxed-out%20credit%20cards%2C%20as%20well%20as%20significant%20car%20and%20student%20debt.%20In%20her%20second%20episode%2C%20posted%20around%20four%20months%20later%2C%20she%20said%20she'd%20paid%20off%20three%20cards%20and%20was%20on%20the%20right%20track%20to%20a%20more%20responsible%20financial%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHammer's%20advice%20is%20just%20the%20start%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Hammer's%20advice%20is%20just%20a%20starting%20point%2C%20as%20other%20former%20guests%20have%20found%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERon%2C%2033%20from%20Nashville%2C%20appeared%20on%20%26quot%3BFinancial%20Audit%26quot%3B%20in%20June%2C%20where%20Hammer%20went%20through%20his%20%2470%2C000%20of%20credit-card%2C%20car%2C%20and%20student%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERon%2C%20who%20doesn't%20share%20his%20surname%20publicly%2C%20told%20Insider%20Hammer%20helped%20show%20him%20%26quot%3Bhow%20bad%26quot%3B%20his%20situation%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20one%20thing%20going%20through%20your%20budget%20yourself%2C%20you%20can%20lie%20to%20yourself%20and%20say%20that%20this%20one%20'just%20that%20one%20time%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20someone%20else%20going%20through%20it%2C%20someone%20who%20doesn't%20know%20you%20and%20isn't%20a%20family%20member%20that%20wants%20to%20spare%20your%20feelings%2C%20there's%20no%20hiding%20or%20justifying%20anything.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERon%20said%20that%20after%20speaking%20to%20Hammer%20he%20stopped%20making%20excuses%20for%20his%20spending%2C%20from%20hard%20partying%20and%20a%20Mountain%20Dew%20habit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he's%20seeking%20a%20second%20job%20now%2C%20and%20has%20tried%20to%20curb%20wasting%20money%20on%20food%20and%20drink.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20hasn't%20found%20it%20that%20easy%20to%20make%20progress.%20While%20he%20found%20a%20second%20job%2C%20he%20ended%20up%20leaving%20his%20initial%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20still%20looking%20for%20more%20work%2C%20but%20with%20the%20economy%20not%20being%20that%20great%2C%20it's%20very%20difficult%20to%20find%20a%20job%20in%20the%20hours%20that%20I%20have%20available%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BNot%20to%20mention%20a%20job%20that%20uses%20the%20business%20degree%20that%20I%20spent%20all%20that%20time%20and%20money%20getting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20he's%20gained%20a%20new%20perspective%2C%20that%20doesn't%20change%20the%20fact%20it's%20hard%20to%20find%20work%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJob%20searching%20is%20difficult%2C%20getting%20ahead%20of%20bad%20financial%20mistakes%20in%20the%20past%20is%20difficult%2C%20finding%20friends%20and%20dates%20that%20understand%20that%20I%20don't%20have%20the%20money%20to%20do%20things%20is%20difficult%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20is%20difficult.%26quot%3B%20Hammer%20can't%20change%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESome%20guests%20have%20had%20issues%20afterwards%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJuan%20Colmenares%20went%20on%20%26quot%3BFinancial%20Audit%26quot%3B%20in%20April%2C%20shortly%20after%20he%20started%20his%20own%20YouTube%20channel%20that%20focuses%20on%20financial%20mistakes%20to%20avoid%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bbut%20it's%20in%20Spanish%20for%20the%20Hispanic%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColmenares%2C%20a%2030-year-old%20living%20in%20Florida%2C%20was%20making%20%24110%2C000%20per%20year%2C%20but%20rated%20himself%20a%202%20out%20of%2010%20for%20financial%20literacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20his%20good%20income%2C%20Colmenares%20had%20multiple%20credit%20cards%20and%20was%20over-spending.%20He%20had%20also%20spent%20%2415%2C000%20on%20his%20wedding%20the%20previous%20year.%20His%20minimum%20monthly%20payments%20for%20his%20debts%20were%20setting%20him%20back%20over%20%241%2C200%20per%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20also%20didn't%20have%20a%20work%20permit%20when%20he%20came%20to%20the%20US%20from%20Venezuela%2C%20and%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20had%20struggled%20and%20racked%20up%20debt%20restarting%20their%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColmenares%20told%20Insider%20they%20were%20in%20a%20better%20situation%20now.%20Part%20of%20it%20was%20Hammer's%20advice%2C%20but%20another%20big%20change%20would%20likely%20have%20come%20anyway%20%E2%80%94%20his%20wife%20finished%20training%20to%20be%20a%20dental%20hygienist%2C%20and%20her%20new%20salary%20doubled%20their%20household%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20they%20were%20also%20eating%20out%20less%20and%20making%20fewer%20big%20buys%20on%20a%20whim%2C%20like%20expensive%20wedding%20rings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20committed%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bsnowball%26quot%3B%20method%20of%20paying%20off%20debt%20that%20Hammer%20recommended%20%E2%80%94%20paying%20off%20the%20smallest%20amount%20first%2C%20even%20if%20it%20isn't%20at%20the%20highest%20interest%2C%20to%20create%20a%20sense%20of%20momentum%20as%20each%20debt%20disappears.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20bit%20awkward%20at%20some%20points%2C%26quot%3B%20however%2C%20Colmenares%20said%20of%20his%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHammer%20seemed%20disorganised%2C%20Colmenares%20said%2C%20having%20not%20reviewed%20any%20of%20his%20paperwork%20beforehand.%20They%20started%20the%20episode%20late.%20A%20lot%20was%20cut%2C%20Colmenares%20said%2C%20because%20Hammer%20was%20trying%20to%20find%20the%20right%20documents%2C%20and%20there%20were%20papers%20all%20over%20the%20floor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColmenares%20also%20noticed%20that%20his%20personal%20information%2C%20like%20his%20employer%20and%20address%2C%20were%20visible%20as%20Hammer%20showed%20the%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20wife%20basically%20got%20doxxed%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Colmenares%2C%20with%20viewers%20finding%20her%20on%20social%20media%20and%20reaching%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20was%20very%20intense%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20because%20they%20both%20suffer%20from%20anxiety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20their%20immigration%20process%20too%2C%20which%20brought%20them%20some%20racial%20abuse%20from%20people%20telling%20them%20to%20go%20back%20to%20where%20they%20came%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColmenares%20said%20he%20asked%20Hammer%20to%20blur%20the%20parts%20of%20the%20video%20where%20his%20information%20was%20visible%2C%20but%20Hammer%20%26quot%3Bwouldn't%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%20Hammer%20addressed%20one%20of%20seven%20moments%20Colmenares%20highlighted%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20just%20never%20cared%20after%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColmenares'%20experience%20lines%20up%20with%20another%20former%20guest%2C%20whom%20Insider%20is%20not%20naming%20for%20privacy%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20Hammer%20ignored%20her%20request%20to%20have%20her%20interview%20taken%20down%20from%20YouTube%2C%20and%20that%20he%20then%20blocked%20her%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20told%20Insider%20she%20%26quot%3Bimmediately%20received%20hateful%20and%20harmful%20messages%26quot%3B%20after%20her%20interview%20was%20posted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20humiliating%20and%20there%20was%20nothing%20I%20could%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20Caleb%20was%20not%20really%20sympathetic%20to%20the%20situation%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColmenares%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20say%20something%20on%20his%20own%20pages%20about%20Hammer%20ignoring%20his%20requests%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bhe%20made%20me%20sign%20a%20document%20that%20basically%20says%20I%20can't%20say%20anything%20bad%20about%20him%20on%20social%20media.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Colmenares%20asked%20for%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20agreement%20for%20his%20lawyer%20to%20see%2C%20Hammer%20%26quot%3Bstopped%20responding%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20He%20speculated%20that%20Hammer%20may%20not%20have%20the%20original%20any%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20anyone%20thinking%20of%20going%20on%20the%20show%2C%20Colmenares%20said%20they%20should%20assume%20the%20same%20might%20happen%20to%20them%2C%20and%20protect%20themselves%20and%20their%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHammer%20was%20blowing%20up%20at%20the%20time.%20In%20the%20past%20year%2C%20he's%20grown%20from%20just%20under%2040%2C000%20subscribers%20to%20750%2C000.%20Colmenares%20said%20he%20thinks%20this%20is%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20disorganization%20he%20noticed%2C%20because%20Hammer%20seemed%20to%20be%20under%20%26quot%3Ba%20lot%20of%20stress.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20didn't%20know%20how%20to%20manage%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe's%20young%2C%20he's%20just%20all%20over%20the%20place.%20And%20we%2C%20the%20interviewee%2C%20obviously%20speaking%20just%20for%20myself%20in%20this%20case%2C%20we%20felt%20that%20we%20got%20the%20backhand%20of%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHopefully%20he%20gets%20that%20sorted%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20Hammer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPeople%20usually%20know%20what%20they're%20signing%20up%20for%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHammer%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20list%20of%20questions%20from%20Insider%20for%20this%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fcaleb-hammer-uses-own-past-money-problems-help-people-debt-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20previous%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20he%20said%20he%20has%20%26quot%3Ba%20lot%20of%20respect%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20people%20who%20come%20on%20his%20show%20and%20%26quot%3Brecognize%20the%20terror%20of%20their%20situation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20they're%20doing%2C%20and%20what%20the%20goal%20of%20the%20show%20is%20doing%2C%20is%20putting%20their%20situation%20on%20display%20so%20that%20people%20who%20relate%20to%20their%20situation%20can%20hopefully%20get%20into%20a%20better%20place%20and%20follow%20the%20same%20solutions%20that%20are%20laid%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20why%20I%20dig%20into%20people%20so%20much%20so%20they%20can%20really%20realize%20how%20scary%20the%20situation%20is.%20It%20benefits%20the%20people%20who%20are%20watching%20because%20they%20can%20fix%20their%20situations.%20Or%20if%20they're%20going%20down%20that%20path%20that%20would%20land%20them%20into%20that%20situation%2C%20they%20can%20start%20turning%20it%20around%20quicker%20than%20if%20they%20were%20in%20it%20already.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20do%20more%20follow-up%20episodes%20with%20people%2C%20but%20has%20struggled%20to%20find%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20try%20my%20best%20to%20keep%20in%20touch%20with%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20promise%20I'm%20not%20ignoring%20them%20if%20they%20do%20reach%20out%20and%20it%20takes%20me%20a%20little%20bit%20to%20get%20back%20to%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Hammer's%20platform%20has%20grown%2C%20so%20has%20the%20criticism.%20His%20subreddit%20is%20very%20active%2C%20and%20while%20it%20is%20mostly%20fans%20that%20post%20there%20and%20play%20%26quot%3BHammer%20bingo%26quot%3B%20with%20some%20of%20his%20catchphrases%20(%26quot%3Bnot%20a%20credit%20card%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bdying%20on%20the%20Walmart%20floor%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bbullshit%20spending)%2C%20it%20has%20also%20attracted%20people%20who%20take%20issue%20with%20his%20style.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20say%20the%20berating%20is%20unhelpful%2C%20and%20Hammer%20sometimes%20goes%20too%20far%2C%20causing%20upset%20in%20already%20vulnerable%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBell%20said%20he%20probably%20doesn't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20it%20too%20much%2C%20though%2C%20as%20most%20people%20know%20what%20they're%20signing%20up%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20went%20in%20there%20fully%20expecting%20just%20to%20be%20torn%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20any%20situation%20of%20financially%20surviving%20in%20this%20harsh%20world%20of%20capitalism%2C%20you%20definitely%20need%20the%20kick%20in%20the%20head.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaleb-hammers-interviews-what-happened-next-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698401485000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https