ates%2C%20and%20recession%20fears%2C%20and%20will%20emerge%20as%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20beneficiaries%20of%20the%20artificial-intelligence%20boom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20trying%20to%20take%20anything%20away%20from%20the%20Magnificent%20Seven%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20a%20super-diversified%20portfolio%2C%26quot%3B%20Jim%20Worden%20told%20Insider%20this%20week%2C%20noting%20all%20seven%20are%20in%20tech%20or%20have%20tech-related%20businesses.%20Worden%20is%20the%20CIO%20of%20The%20Wealth%20Consulting%20Group%2C%20which%20manages%20over%20%245%20billion%20in%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBerkshire%20commands%20a%20larger%20market%20capitalization%20than%20Tesla%20or%20Meta%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20counted%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Magnificent%20Seven%20because%20it's%20not%20a%20fast-growing%20technology%20company.%20Including%20it%20would%20provide%20significant%20diversification%20to%20the%20group%20of%20high-flying%20stocks%2C%20Worden%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuffett's%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarren-buffett-berkshire-hathaway-consumer-spending-recession-economy-rates-inflation-2023-8%5C%22%3Eowns%20scores%20of%20businesses%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20a%20large%20swath%20of%20sectors%2C%20including%20insurance%2C%20railroads%2C%20utilities%2C%20manufacturing%2C%20real%20estate%2C%20retail%2C%20and%20services.%20It%20also%20holds%20roughly%20%24350%20billion%20worth%20of%20stocks%2C%20including%20multibillion-dollar%20stakes%20in%20Apple%2C%20Bank%20of%20America%2C%20Chevron%2C%20Coca-Cola%2C%20and%20Kraft%20Heinz.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20Berkshire%20lacks%20in%20growth%20and%20innovation%2C%20it%20makes%20up%20for%20with%20lots%20of%20other%20advantages%2C%20Worden%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20Buffett%20and%20his%20team%20use%20the%20premiums%20collected%20from%20their%20insurance%20operations%20as%20a%20source%20of%20permanent%20capital%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20be%20patient%20and%20opportunistic%20in%20t