202023%20Billboard%20Music%20Awards%20have%20been%20announced%2C%20with%20K-pop%20artists%20dominating%20the%20list.%20BTS%20members%20are%20nominated%20both%20as%20a%20group%20and%20as%20solo%20artists%20in%20various%20categories.%20BTS'%20Jungkook%2C%20Jimin%2C%20Suga%2C%20are%20in%20the%20running%20with%20K-pop%20artists%20like%20Stray%20Kids%2C%20NewJeans%2C%20BLACKPINK%2C%20TWICE%2C%20and%20TXT.%20The%20awards%20will%20feature%20new%20categories%2C%20including%20top%20global%20K-pop%20artist%2C%20top%20K-pop%20tour%2C%20top%20K-pop%20album%2C%20and%20top%20global%20K-pop%20song.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fk-pop%2Fmusic%2Fnews%2Fbts-jungkook-jimin-suga-blackpink-and-more-earn-nominations-for-2023-billboard-music-awards%2Farticleshow%2F104752236.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20an%20employment%20attorney%20who%20rejects%2098%25%20of%20inquiries.%20Here%20are%20the%20wrongful%20termination%20cases%20that%20actually%20stand%20a%20chance.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221027%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jonathan%20Pollard%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653aaf8796f7540cd066e2af%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJonathan%20Pollard%20is%20an%20employment%20attorney.%3Cp%3EPollard%20PLLC%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJonathan%20Pollard%20is%C2%A0an%20employment%20attorney%20who%20receives%20hundreds%20of%20inquiries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20writes%20that%20most%20employees%20with%20grievances%20are%20entitled%2C%20dramatic%2C%20and%20looking%20for%20a%20payday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPollard%20writes%20that%20most%20people%20who%20reach%20out%20have%20absolutely%20no%20case.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20an%20employment%20attorney%20who%20has%20represented%20hundreds%20of%20employees%20and%20litigated%20many%20cases%20over%20the%20past%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20own%20a%20law%20firm%20with%20offices%20in%20Fort%20Lauderdale%2C%20Miami%2C%20and%20shortly%20in%20St.%20Louis%2C%20Missouri.%20These%20days%2C%20most%20of%20our%20work%20involves%20representing%20employees%20in%20pursuing%20cases%20against%20corporate%20America%20for%20discrimination%2C%20sexual%20harassment%2C%20sexual%20assault%2C%20and%20retaliation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20believe%20in%20the%20work%20that%20we%20do.%20There%20are%20very%20real%20instances%20of%20corporate%20America%20engaging%20in%20misconduct%2C%20and%20we%20aggressively%20pursue%20those%20real%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20also%20believe%20that%20many%20%E2%80%94%20probably%20most%20%E2%80%94%20employees%20with%20workplace%20grievances%20are%20entitled%2C%20dramatic%2C%20maladjusted%2C%20delusional%2C%20and%20just%20looking%20for%20a%20payday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20anyone%20can%20say%20that%20with%20authority%2C%20it's%20me.%20Each%20week%2C%20I%20would%20estimate%20our%20firm%20gets%20more%20than%20500%20inquiries%20a%20week%20on%20employment%20cases.%20We%20reject%20about%2098%25%20of%20these.%20The%20numbers%20break%20down%20as%20follows%20and%20the%20percentages%20are%20approximations%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E75%25%20are%20clearly%20frivolous%20and%20there%20is%20no%20case%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E20%25%20are%20plausible%20cases%20that%20I%20don't%20pursue%20due%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20evidence%20or%20unfavorable%20law%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E5%25%20are%20real%20cases%20%E2%80%94%20of%20these%20real%20cases%2C%20I%20only%20take%202-3%25%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20frivolous%20cases%3A%20Most%20people%20who%20reach%20out%20have%20no%20case%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20categories%20of%20people%20make%20up%20the%20first%20group%20of%20inquiries%20(the%2075%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E1.%20People%20who%20feel%20that%20someone%20was%20mean%20to%20them%20at%20work%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20fired%20and%20don't%20like%20the%20reason%20why%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20think%20they%20did%20a%20good%20job%2C%20or%20at%20least%20a%20not%20fireable%20job%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20never%20given%20a%20final%20warning%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20don't%20feel%20valued%20or%20%26quot%3Bvalidated%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20people%20feel%20like%20their%20situation%20is%20terribly%20unfair%20and%20hurtful.%20In%20these%20types%20of%20cases%2C%20the%20details%20may%20change%2C%20but%20the%20general%20story%20is%20always%20the%20same%3A%20Company%20X%20recruited%20Fred%20and%20promised%20him%20the%20world%20(not%20in%20writing%2C%20of%20course).%20The%20company%20never%20trained%20Fred%20on%20key%20responsibilities.%20The%20company%20threw%20Fred%20to%20the%20wolves%20and%20made%20him%20figure%20things%20out%20on%20his%20own.%20Fred%20did%20his%20best.%20But%20his%20direct%20boss%20never%20empowered%20him.%20Fred's%20voice%20and%20opinions%20were%20not%20heard%20and%20validated.%20Fred%20was%20terminated.%20And%20his%20feelings%20are%20hurt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EModern%20society%20has%20convinced%20people%20that%20feelings%20and%20rights%20are%20interchangeable.%20But%20that%20is%20not%20true.%20Laws%20exist%20to%20protect%20rights%2C%20not%20feelings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E2.%20People%20who%20received%20critical%20feedback%20or%20were%20put%20on%20a%20PIP%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20are%20aggrieved%20%3Cem%3Esolely%3C%2Fem%3E%20because%20a%20company%20has%20given%20them%20critical%20feedback%20on%20their%20performance.%20These%20people%20have%20no%20concrete%20allegations%20of%2C%20e.g.%2C%20discrimination%2C%20retaliation%2C%20or%20other%20corporate%20misconduct.%20But%20they%20have%20been%20fired%2C%20given%20a%20negative%20performance%20review%2C%20or%20placed%20on%20a%20%26quot%3BPIP%20plan.%26quot%3BLet's%20call%20our%20example%20Joe.%20Joe%20is%20in%20his%20mid%2040s.%20Joe%20has%20worked%20at%20Company%20X%20for%2015%20years%20in%20sales%20management.%20And%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20his%20life%2C%20Joe%20has%20been%20told%20that%20his%20performance%20is%20not%20satisfactory.%20Company%20X%20placed%20him%20on%20a%20PIP%20plan.%20Joe's%20immediate%20reaction%20is%20not%20to%20evaluate%20his%20performance%20or%20consider%20whether%20he%20may%20be%20deficient%20in%20certain%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20like%20Joe%20automatically%20attribute%20this%20to%20something%20illegal%20and%20nefarious%20(without%20specific%20facts%20supporting%20that%20conclusion).%20They%20want%20to%20%26quot%3Btake%20legal%20action%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bfigure%20out%20their%20rights.%26quot%3B%20They%20cannot%20articulate%20any%20actual%20corporate%20wrongdoing.%20Instead%2C%20the%20perceived%20wrong%20is%20solely%20the%20employment%20action%20taken%20against%20them.%20And%20the%20harm%20to%20their%20feelings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20plausible%20cases%3A%20Some%20people%20have%20viable%20cases%2C%20but%20they%20aren't%20worth%20pursuing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPlausible%20cases%20involve%20a%20situation%20where%20something%20seems%20improper%20but%20there%20is%20no%20compelling%2C%20direct%20evidence%20and%2For%20the%20law%20on%20that%20specific%20situation%20is%20not%20in%20not%20favorable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20situations%20where%20the%20employee%20might%20have%20a%20viable%20case%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20a%20case%20that%20is%20strong%20enough%20for%20us%20to%20pursue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bucket%20of%20plausible%20cases%20we%20receive%20is%20just%20above%2020%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20real%20cases%3A%20A%20small%20percentage%20are%20from%20people%20who%20clearly%20have%20been%20legally%20wronged%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20remaining%205%25%20are%20real%20legal%20cases%20arising%20out%20of%20workplace%20issues%20and%20corporate%20misconduct.%20These%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EDiscrimination%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ERetaliation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ESexual%20harassment%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ESexual%20assault%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EDefamation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20potential%20clients%20are%20good%2C%20solid%20people%20who%20seem%20reasonable%20and%20honest.%20At%20their%20jobs%2C%20they%20have%20been%20treated%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20is%20morally%20and%20legally%20wrong%2C%20inhumane%2C%20and%20sometimes%20utterly%20horrific.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20we%20do%20not%20take%20all%20these%20cases%20because%20of%20economic%20realities.%20Many%20small%20companies%20that%20engage%20in%20the%20worst%20forms%20of%20misconduct%20do%20not%20have%20sufficient%20assets%20or%20insurance.%20A%20%2410%20million%20judgment%20is%20worthless%20unless%20you%20can%20collect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20chased%20big%20judgments%20through%20layers%20of%20shell%20companies.%20I%20don't%20do%20that%20anymore.%20This%20is%20reality%3A%20It%20is%20not%20my%20job%20to%20play%20nursemaid%20to%20the%20universe%20and%20tilt%20at%20windmills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20cases%20we%20accept%3A%20a%20small%20percentage%20that%20meets%20specific%20metrics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20leaves%20roughly%202%25%20to%203%25%20of%20cases%20that%20we%20accept.%20These%20days%2C%20most%20of%20those%20cases%20fall%20into%20a%20handful%20of%20specific%20buckets%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ERace%20discrimination%20(particularly%20against%20Black%20people)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EAge%20discrimination%20(particularly%20against%20folks%2060%20and%20older)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ESexual%20harassment%20or%20outright%20sexual%20assault%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20these%20cases%20also%20have%20a%20retaliation%20component%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20see%20cases%20from%20every%20industry.%20But%20some%20of%20the%20ugliest%2C%20most%20egregious%20cases%20come%20out%20of%20the%20broader%20construction%20industry%3A%20workers%20constantly%20called%20the%20N-word%20and%20told%20that%20they%20would%20be%20killed%20if%20it%20was%20still%20the%20good%20old%20days%3B%20construction%20foreman%20riding%20around%20on%20his%20golf%20cart%2C%20gun%20strapped%20to%20his%20waist%2C%20shouting%20racial%20slurs%20at%20black%20workers%20digging%20in%20a%20trench%3B%20rampant%20sexual%20harassment%20and%20sexual%20assault%3B%20women%20raped%20by%20a%20coworker%20on%20a%20job%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20these%20real%20cases%2C%20where%20we%20represent%20good%20people%20who%20have%20basically%20been%20beaten%20down%20and%20abused%2C%20we%20will%20go%20to%20the%20ends%20of%20the%20earth%20to%20vindicate%20their%20rights.%20But%20even%20then%2C%20litigation%2C%20trial%2C%20and%20even%20a%20big%20jury%20verdict%20won't%20undo%20whatever%20damage%20has%20been%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20best%2C%20litigation%20gets%20you%20a%20chunk%20of%20money.%20You%20must%20find%20and%20make%20your%20own%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJonathan%20Pollard%20is%20an%20employment%20attorney%20based%20in%20Fort%20Lauderdale%2C%20Florida.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwrongful-termination-cases-employment-attorney-rejections-win-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698399062000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653ab0200487ff031caf9c0c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwrongful-termination-cases-employment-attorney-rejections-win-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Most%20wrongful%20termination%20cases%20involve%20delusional%20grievances%20or%20employees%20looking%20for%20a%20payday.%20An%20attorney%20explains%20what%20makes%20a%20good%20case.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com