k%20a%20surfing%20lesson%20offered%20by%20the%20shop%20he%20managed.%20We've%20always%20had%20the%20urge%20to%20travel%20together%2C%20and%20we%20were%20inspired%20by%20all%20the%20nomads%20and%20van%20lifers%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fthehealthfulnomad%2F%3Fhl%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esaw%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Joseph%20is%20also%20an%20avid%20windsurfer%20and%20had%20been%20wanting%20to%20travel%20to%20more%20windsurfing%20spots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20bought%20a%20'skoolie'%20in%20July%202021%20to%20make%20our%20dream%20a%20reality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22758%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20school%20bus%20in%20the%20desert%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653a925a356802a56be4d7b5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22569%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWillow%20the%20Skoolie.%3Cp%3ECarly%20Wesolowski%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20took%20the%20leap%20and%20bought%20our%20traveling%20home%2C%20Willow%20the%20Skoolie%2C%20a%202004%2025-foot%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-bought-old-school-bus-turned-it-into-skoolie-airbnb-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einternational%20school%20bus%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20%2422%2C500%20from%20a%20Texas%20couple%20we%20found%20on%20Facebook.%20We%20put%20%242%2C000%20into%20it%20when%20we%20bought%20it%20for%20a%20new%20battery%2C%20a%20new%20electrical%20system%2C%20a%20new%20roof%20rack%20and%20Thule%20rooftop%20storage%2C%20and%20a%20bed-to-dinette%20conversion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20waited%20to%20move%20into%20it%20until%20April%202022%20because%20Joseph%20was%20finishing%20his%20last%20season%20as%20a%20manager%20of%20the%20surf%20shop%2C%20and%20I%20was%20wrapping%20up%20a%20research%20project%20at%20work%20in%20Ohio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20we%20moved%20in%20and%20started%20traveling%2C%20it%20cost%20about%20%24500%20a%20month%20for%20gas%20and%20other%20repairs%20and%20about%20%24250%20a%20month%20for%20groceries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20autumn%2C%20we%20knew%20that%20we%20would%20run%20out%20of%20savings%20if%20we%20didn't%20find%20ways%20to%20make%20money.%20We%20found%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaskrabbit-users-share-best-advice-make-thousands-every-month%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETaskrabbit%20app%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20created%20profiles%20while%20we%20were%20in%20Seattle%20in%20October%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20started%20with%20several%20skills%20on%20my%20profile%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20frequently%20hired%20for%20indoor%20painting%2C%20yard%20work%2C%20and%20organization%2C%20but%20I%20was%20most%20often%20hired%20for%20cleaning%2C%20which%20became%20my%20focus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoseph%20started%20out%20by%20offering%20indoor%20painting%20and%20yard%20work.%20As%20time%20went%20on%2C%20he%20slowly%20started%20jumping%20into%20furniture%20assembly%2C%20cleaning%2C%20personal-assistant%20work%2C%20packing%2C%20and%20unpacking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20hours%20varied%2C%20but%20I%20was%20working%20the%20most%20when%20we%20were%20in%20San%20Diego.%20I%20did%20about%2020%20hours%20a%20week%2C%20and%20Joseph%20averaged%2010%20to%2015%20hours.%20My%20income%20averaged%20%24800%20a%20month%2C%20and%20Joseph%20averaged%20about%20%24500.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere%20are%20the%20biggest%20downsides%20to%20living%20on%20the%20bus%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20in%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-family-tiny-home-roof-school-bus-diy-space-kids-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eskoolie%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20presents%20you%20with%20many%20chores%20and%20challenges%2C%20but%20we%20felt%20the%20trade-off%20was%20more%20than%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20a%20few%20times%20when%20we%20struggled%20to%20find%20clean%20water%20to%20refill%20our%20tanks.%20We%20also%20dealt%20with%20our%20battery%20occasionally%20running%20low%20on%20power%2C%20so%20we%20would%20turn%20off%20the%20fridge%20to%20save%20the%20battery%20until%20we%20could%20recharge%20at%20places%20such%20as%20campsites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20a%20shower%20and%20a%20bathroom%20%E2%80%94%20we%20just%20needed%20to%20be%20cognizant%20of%20how%20much%20water%20we%20were%20using%2C%20especially%20if%20we%20were%20in%20a%20more%20remote%20area%20and%20didn't%20have%20immediate%20access%20to%20a%20dump%20station%20or%20water%20refill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20places%20to%20park%20overnight%2C%20especially%20in%20cities%2C%20was%20also%20a%20significant%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDespite%20the%20challenges%2C%20we%20got%20to%20see%20so%20many%20places%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20traveled%20and%20lived%20in%20San%20Diego%3B%20Seattle%3B%20the%20Outer%20Banks%3B%20Washington%2C%20DC%3B%20Columbus%2C%20Ohio%3B%20Northern%20Michigan%20and%20the%20Upper%20Peninsula%3B%20Missoula%2C%20Montana%3B%20Skokomish%2C%20Washington%3B%20San%20Francisco%3B%20and%20Los%20Angeles.%20San%20Diego%20was%20the%20best%20city%20for%20Taskrabbit%20gigs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20lovers%20of%20the%20outdoors%2C%20and%20Taskrabbit%20helped%20us%20see%2011%20national%20parks.%20We'd%20work%20a%20few%20weeks%20in%20a%20city%2C%20including%20Seattle%2C%20then%20take%20a%20couple%20of%20weeks%20to%20visit%20a%20nearby%20national%20park.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20about%20a%20year%20of%20traveling%2C%20in%20July%2C%20we%20both%20moved%20back%20home%20to%20focus%20on%20developing%20our%20careers.%20I'm%20in%20Colorado%20finishing%20my%20master's%20degree%2C%20and%20Joseph%20is%20in%20San%20Diego%20working%20in%20yacht%20sales.%20We%20hope%20to%20travel%20full%20time%20again%20in%20the%20near%20future%20and%20are%20working%20on%20saving%20to%20buy%20a%20new%20van%20in%202025%2C%20when%20I%20graduate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20still%20do%20Taskrabbit%20gigs%20as%20needed%20and%20plan%20to%20work%20on%20the%20platform%20more%20consistently%20once%20we%20return%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvan-life-hard-shower-bathroom-pros-cons-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evan%20life%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere's%20my%20best%20advice%20for%20being%20a%20nomadic%20Tasker%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20who%20are%20also%20interested%20in%20traveling%20and%20being%20a%20Tasker%2C%20I%20recommend%20having%20reliable%20transportation%20such%20as%20a%20bike%2C%20scooter%2C%20or%20e-bike%2C%20or%20learning%20how%20to%20use%20public%20transportation%20in%20the%20city%20you're%20in.%20Because%20of%20the%20size%20of%20our%20vehicle%2C%20we%20sometimes%20had%20to%20get%20creative%20with%20transportation%20to%20job%20sites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20using%20public%20transit%2C%20I%20also%20recommend%20making%20sure%20your%20Tasker%20map%20range%20is%20drawn%20to%20include%20neighborhoods%20and%20areas%20that%20are%20easily%20accessible%20by%20the%20public-transportation%20system%20so%20there's%20less%20stress%20during%20your%20commute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20surprised%20that%20working%20for%20Taskrabbit%20gave%20us%20networking%20opportunities%20with%20clients.%20I%20was%20able%20to%20find%20people%20who%20were%20also%20in%20the%20health%20and%20wellness%20space%20and%20form%20connections%20and%20collaborations%20as%20a%20health%20coach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoseph%20networked%20with%20Taskrabbit%20clients%20by%20finding%20people%20who%20might%20be%20interested%20in%20selling%20or%20purchasing%20a%20yacht%20one%20day.%20If%20you're%20a%20Tasker%2C%20be%20open%20to%20the%20opportunities%20that%20can%20come%20from%20the%20people%20who%20hire%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-used-taskrabbit-fund-year-long-school-bus-trip-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusines