0been%20lackluster%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20the%20government%20has%20more%20trouble%20finding%20buyers%20for%20new%20Treasurys%2C%20yields%20will%20rise%20to%20attract%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22787%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%2210-year%20treasury%20yield%2010-26-23%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653ab2700487ff031cafa138%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22329%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%2010-year%20Treasury%20yield%20exceeded%205%25%20on%20Oct.%2023%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%202007.%3Cp%3EInvesting.com%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERetail%20investors%20can%20gain%20exposure%20to%20these%20assets%20by%20buying%20into%20Treasury%20ETFs%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fetfs%2Fishares-20-year-treasury-bond-etf-us4642874329%5C%22%3ETLT%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20this%20is%20a%20much%20more%20volatile%20trade%20than%20buying%20an%20actual%20bond.%20While%20the%20value%20of%20bonds%20can%20see%20daily%20market%20fluctuations%20that%20impact%20the%20price%20of%20ETFs%2C%20the%20US%20has%20never%20defaulted%20on%20its%20debt%2C%20making%20the%20purchase%20of%20Treasurys%20themselves%20a%20nearly%20risk-free%20proposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can%20get%20more%20than%204%25%20on%20Treasurys%2C%20that%20makes%20you%20think%20twice%20about%20a%20lot%20of%20risky%20investments%2C%26quot%3B%20Matthew%20Liebman%2C%20founding%20partner%20at%20Amplius%20Wealth%20Advisors%2C%20recently%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Ffeatures%2F2023-investment-mistakes-to-avoid-guide%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Bloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20two%20main%20avenues%20an%20investor%20can%20use%20to%20get%20ahold%20of%20these%20securities%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETreasuryDirect.gov%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.treasurydirect.gov%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eofficial%20government%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20central%20resource%20for%20any%20investor%20looking%20to%20purchase%20Treasurys%20electronically.%20Setting%20up%20an%20account%20only%20requires%20a%20Social%20Security%20number%20(or%20another%20form%20of%20tax%20identification)%2C%20email%20address%2C%20and%20bank%20account%20information.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20an%20account%20is%20active%2C%20investors%20can%20choose%20which%20asset%20to%20purchase%2C%20organized%20by%20the%20duration%20of%20the%20Treasury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShorter-term%20Treasurys%20like%20T-bills%2C%20while%20have%20a%20duration%20of%20less%20than%20a%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftreasurydirect.gov%2Fmarketable-securities%2Ftreasury-bills%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonly%20pay%20interest%20at%20the%20security's%20mature%20date%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20long-dated%20Treasurys%20give%20investors%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftreasurydirect.gov%2Fmarketable-securities%2Ftreasury-notes%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWe%2520sell%2520Treasury%2520Notes%2520for%2Csix%2520months%2520until%2520they%2520mature.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efixed%20interest%20payment%3C%2Fa%3E%20every%20six%20months%20until%20the%20security%20matures.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20a%20security%20is%20selected%2C%20investors%20can%20choose%20how%20much%20of%20it%20they%20wish%20to%20buy%2C%20and%20the%20Treasurys%20are%20sold%20to%20them%20at%20the%20next%20auction.%20T-bill%20sales%20happen%20weekly%2C%20notes%20that%20mature%20in%20two%20to%2010%20years%20are%20sold%20are%20monthly%2C%20and%20bonds%20with%2020-%20or%2030-year%20durations%20are%20auctioned%20four%20times%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETreasury%20purchases%20can%20be%20reinvested%20automatically%20at%20the%20next%20auction%2C%20once%20the%20original%20asset%20matures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBrokerages%20and%20banks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBuying%20bonds%20via%20on%20TreasuryDirect%20has%20a%20few%20drawbacks.%20For%20instance%2C%20holders%20can't%20sell%20their%20bonds%20directly%20from%20a%20TreasuryDirect%20account.%20Instead%2C%20they%20first%20have%20to%20be%20transferred%20to%20a%20broker%20or%20dealer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20TreasuryDirect%20website%20only%20sells%20new%20Treasurys%2C%20and%20previously-issued%20bonds%20will%20not%20be%20found%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20greater%20access%20to%20the%20Treasury%20market%2C%20investors%20can%20turn%20to%20brokerages%20and%20some%20commercial%20banks%2C%20which%20act%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Fbond-yields-treasury-market-liquidity-all-to-all-trading-debt-2023-4%5C%22%3Eprimary%20intermediaries%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20US%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20their%20services%20may%20come%20with%20a%20commission%20or%20require%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fool.com%2Finvesting%2Fhow-to-invest%2Fbonds%2Ftreasury-bonds%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMany%2520brokers%2520allow%2520you%2520to%2Cincrements%2520on%2520the%2520TreasuryDirect%2520website.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eminimum%20purchase%3C%2Fa%3E%20amount%2C%20these%20dealers%20allow%20investors%20to%20participate%20in%20both%20Treasury%20auctions%20and%20the%20secondary%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20using%20a%20broker%20to%20buy%20bonds%20in%20the%20secondary%20market%2C%20investors%20can%20also%20add%20Treasury%20assets%20into%20tax-free%20accounts%2C%20such%20as%20a%20Roth%20IRA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftreasury-bond-market-how-to-invest-5-percent-yield-treasurydirect-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698397202000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2