a33XkAA9juX.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJaipur%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Congress%20party%20has%20released%20its%20third%20list%20of%20candidates%20for%20Rajasthan%2C%20with%2019%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThree%20of%20these%20candidates%20are%20Sachin%20Pilot%20loyalists%3A%20Gajraj%20Khatana%20from%20Bandikui%2C%20Rakesh%20Parek%20from%20Masuda%2C%20and%20Harish%20Meena%20from%20Deoli%20Uniyaar.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20list%2C%20the%20party%20had%20announced%2033%20candidates%2C%20and%20in%20the%20second%20list%2C%20revealed%2043%20candidates%20for%20the%20200%20legislative%20assembly%20seats.%20With%20the%20release%20of%20this%20third%20list%2C%20the%20party%20has%20declared%20candidates%20for%2095%20out%20of%20the%20200%20assembly%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20list%20came%20out%20while%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fgoondagardi-says-ashok-gehlot-as-ed-summons-his-son-raids-rajasthan-congress-chief%5C%22%3Econducting%20raids%20on%20locations%3C%2Fa%3E%20linked%20to%20Rajasthan%20Congress%20president%20Govind%20Singh%20Dotasra%20and%20independent%20MLA%20Om%20Prakash%20Hudla.%20The%20central%20agency%20had%20also%20summoned%20chief%20minister%20Ashok%20Gehlot%E2%80%99s%20son%20for%20questioning%2C%20and%20the%20Congress%20and%20other%20parties%20had%20hit%20out%20at%20the%20BJP%20for%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Egoondagardi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(hooliganism)%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20the%2019%20candidates%20on%20the%20third%20list%2C%20Congress%20has%20nominated%2014%20sitting%20MLAs.%20This%20also%20includes%20independent%20candidates%20Ramkesh%20Meena%2C%20C.L.%20Premi%20Bairwa%20and%20Pusaram%20Godara%2C%20who%20will%20be%20contesting%20from%20Gangapur%2C%20Keshoraipatan%20and%20Ratangarh%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20351px)%2085vw%2C%20351px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22351%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711-300x248.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711-1024x845.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681756%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22290%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeena%20had%20won%20the%20Gangapur%20seat%20in%20the%20previous%20election.%20Premi%20came%20in%20third%20with%2035%2C115%20votes%20from%20Keshoraipatan%20in%202018.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Rakesh%20Boyat%20received%2065%2C477%20votes%20and%20secured%20the%20second%20position%2C%20losing%20to%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Chandrakanta%20Meghwal%2C%20who%20won%20the%20seat%20with%2072%2C596%20votes.%20Pusaram%20Godara%2C%20who%20ran%20independently%20in%20the%20Ratangarh%20seat%2C%20lost%20to%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Abhinesh%20Maharshi.%20In%20this%20contest%2C%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Bhanwarlal%20Pujari%20received%20only%2022%2C791%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDholpur%20MLA%20Shobha%20Rani%20Kushwah%2C%20who%20was%20expelled%20from%20the%20BJP%20for%20cross-voting%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20Congress%20candidate%20in%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20Rajya%20Sabha%20election%2C%20has%20been%20given%20the%20Congress%20ticket%20from%20the%20same%20seat.%20She%20was%20officially%20inducted%20into%20the%20Congress%20at%20an%20election%20rally%20addressed%20by%20Priyanka%20Gandhi%20Vadra%20in%20Jhunjhunu%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20Congress%20has%20chosen%20sitting%20MLA%20Narendra%20Budaniya%20from%20Taranagar%20to%20contest%20against%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20Rajendra%20Rathore.%20This%20year%2C%20Rathore%20has%20changed%20his%20seat%20and%20will%20be%20running%20from%20Taranagar%20instead%20of%20Churu.%20Rathore%20had%20previously%20contested%20and%20won%20the%20Taranagar%20seat%20in%202008%2C%20but%20since%201990%2C%20he%20has%20consistently%20contested%20and%20won%20the%20Churu%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20Nagar%20seat%2C%20Congress%20has%20fielded%20Wajid%20Ali%2C%20who%20had%20previously%20won%20the%20seat%20on%20a%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20ticket.%20In%202019%2C%20Ali%2C%20along%20with%20six%20other%20MLAs%20who%20won%20the%202018%20state%20assembly%20elections%20on%20BSP%20tickets%2C%20joined%20the%20Congress.%20In%202022%2C%20Congress%20entrusted%20Ali%20with%20more%20responsibilities%20by%20appointing%20him%20as%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20Rajasthan%20State%20Food%20Commission%20and%20the%20Bhiwadi%20Urban%20Infrastructure%20Development%20Board.%20In%20the%202018%20election%2C%20Wajib%20Ali%20secured%2062%2C644%20votes%2C%20while%20Nem%20Singh%20from%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%20received%2037%2C177%20votes%2C%20placing%20him%20second.%20The%20BJP%20secured%20the%20third%20position%20with%2034%2C946%20votes%2C%20and%20Congress%20was%20fourth%20with%2031%2C678%20votes.%20It%20will%20be%20interesting%20to%20see%20how%20many%20votes%20Congress%20garners%20this%20time%2C%20with%20Ali%20being%20their%20top%20candidate.%20For%20the%20Nagar%20seat%2C%20BJP%20has%20nominated%20Jawahar%20Singh%20and%20denied%20a%20ticket%20to%20Anita%20Singh%2C%20who%20received%2034%2C946%20votes%20in%20the%20previous%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Karauli%20seat%2C%20Congress%20has%20nominated%20another%20candidate%2C%20Lakhan%20Singh%20Meena%2C%20who%20switched%20from%20the%20BSP.%20Lakhan%20won%20the%20Karauli%20seat%20with%20a%20margin%20of%209%2C562%20votes%20against%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Darshan%20Singh%2C%20while%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Om%20Prakash%20Saini%20received%2047%2C022%20votes%20and%20secured%20the%2