7-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681851%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOrthodox%20Jews%20outside%20the%20BBC%20building%20in%20Central%20London%20showing%20solidarity%20with%20Palestine.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FAlisdare%20Hickson%2FCC%20BY-SA%202.0%20DEED.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20outright%20support%20of%20Israel%20is%20in%20contravention%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20longstanding%20view%20of%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict.%20India%E2%80%99s%20position%20has%20always%20been%2C%20in%20a%20way%2C%20to%20put%20in%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20words%20of%201938%2C%20%E2%80%9CPalestine%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theweek.in%2Fcolumns%2FMani-Shankar-Aiyar%2F2023%2F10%2F21%2Fno-peace-possible-without-justice-to-persecuted-palestinians.html%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.theweek.in%2Fcolumns%2FMani-Shankar-Aiyar%2F2023%2F10%2F21%2Fno-peace-possible-without-justice-to-persecuted-palestinians.html%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1698389932986000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1vwgyUScT2TI0EB-KMAxxo%5C%22%3Ebelongs%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Arabs%20as%20England%20belongs%20to%20the%20English%20and%20France%20to%20the%20French.%E2%80%9D%20Gandhi%20famously%20observed%20that%20Jews%20suffered%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20Christians%2C%20but%20it%20cannot%20be%20compensated%20by%20taking%20away%20the%20land%20of%20Palestinians%20to%20undo%20the%20wrongs%20of%20history.%20Jews%20were%20the%20victims%20of%20anti-semitism%2C%20which%20prevailed%20in%20Europe.%20Among%20many%20roots%20of%20anti-semitism%20was%20the%20feeling%20that%20it%20was%20Jews%20who%20were%20responsible%20for%20the%20crucifixion%20of%20Jesus%20Christ.%20Later%20other%20trade%20rivalries%20were%20added%20to%20this%20resulting%20in%20Adolf%20Hitler%20pursuing%20the%20worst%20forms%20of%20anti-semitism%2C%20by%20massacring%20lakhs%20of%20Jews.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fisrael-palestine-conflict-india-forsakerole-voice-of-moderation%5C%22%3EIsrael-Palestine%20Conflict%3A%20Why%20Has%20India%20Forsaken%20Its%20Role%20as%20a%20Voice%20of%20Moderation%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20displaced%20Jews%20had%20to%20suffer%20a%20lot%20of%20discrimination%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20the%20Zionist%20movement%20taking%20root.%20Theodore%20Herzl%E2%80%99s%20pamphlet%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Jewish%20State%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20a%20conference%20of%20some%20Jews%20in%201897%20in%20Switzerland%E2%80%99s%20Basle%20further%20laid%20the%20foundations%20for%20the%20Zionist%20movement.%20Quoting%20from%20the%20Old%20Testament%20in%20the%20Bible%2C%20Zionists%20declared%20that%20Palestine%20belonged%20to%20Jews%20and%20came%20up%20with%20the%20slogan%2C%20%E2%80%98A%20land%20without%20a%20people%20for%20a%20people%20without%20a%20land%E2%80%99.%20The%20slogan%20completely%20ignored%20the%20fact%20that%20Palestinians%20had%20inhabited%20the%20land%20for%20over%20a%20millennia.%20And%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20Palestinians%20were%20not%20only%20Muslims%20(86%25)%2C%20but%20they%20were%20also%20Christian%20(10%25)%20and%20Jewish%20(4%25).%20In%20the%20aftermath%20of%20that%20conference%2C%20a%20%E2%80%98Jewish%20National%20Fund%E2%80%99%20was%20instituted%2C%20and%20Jews%20from%20around%20the%20world%20began%20to%20relocate%20to%20Palestine%20and%20bought%20lands%20even%20before%20Israel%20was%20established%20in%201948.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20this%20trend%20began%20to%20take%20shape%2C%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Jews%20opposed%20Zionism%2C%20which%20appealed%20to%20Jews%20to%20move%20to%20Palestine%20and%20urged%20specifically%20not%20to%20rent%20or%20resell%20their%20lands%20to%20Arabs.%20The%20intentions%20of%20Zionists%20were%20very%20clear%20right%20from%20the%20start%20that%20they%20wanted%20to%20increase%20their%20numbers%20in%20the%20region.%20As%20their%20numbers%20increased%2C%20Palestine%20came%20under%20the%20British%20mandate%20and%20the%20local%20Arabs%20began%20to%20see%20what%20was%20happening%20to%20their%20land.%20At%20this%20point%2C%20the%20British%20implemented%20its%20Balfour%20Declaration%20of%201917%2C%20which%20supported%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20establishment%20of%20a%20national%20home%20for%20the%20Jewish%20people%20in%20Palestine%E2%80%9D.%20The%20seeds%20for%20the%20present%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict%20were%2C%20thus%2C%20sowed%20by%20the%20British%20colonialists.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJewish%20writer%20Arthur%20Koestler%20described%20the%20Balfour%20Declaration%20in%20the%20most%20succinct%20way%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20the%20most%20improbable%20document%20of%20all%20the%20times.%E2%80%9D%20American-Israeli%20historian%20Martin%20Kramer%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20called%20the%20Declaration%20as%20something%20which%20%E2%80%9Cconstituted%20the%20first%20step%20towards%20the%20objective%20of%20political%20Zionism%E2%80%A6narrow%2C%20conditional%2C%20hedged%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Arab%20resistance%20to%20Jewish%20migration%20and%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20plan%20to%20establish%20a%20Jewish%20national%20home%20in%20Palestine%20began%20in%201936.%20It%20was%2C%20however%2C%20crushed%20by%20the%20British.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20persecution%20of%20Jews%20by%20Hitler%20intensified%20the%20immigration%20of%20Jews%20into%20the%20area%20after%20the%20Second%20World%20War.%20Interestingly%2C%20European%20countries%20and%20America%20did%20not%20encourage%20Jews%20to%20come%20to%20their%20lands.%20In%20due%20course%2C%20the%20historic%20Palestine%20was%20divided%20into%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%2C%20with%20Jerusalem%20and%20Bethlehem%20brought%20under%20international%20control.%20The%20division%20of%20land%20was%20very%20much%20against%20the%20interests%20of%20Arabs%2C%20as%2030%25%20of%20Jews%20who%20occupied%207%25%20of%20the%20land%20were%20given%2055%25%20of%20the%20land.%20Palestinians%20declared%20this%20as%20Al%20Naqba%20(Catastrophe)%20and%20were%20forced%20to%20occupy%2045%25%20of%20the%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-israel-palestine-war-is-a-stain-on-every-one-of-us%5C%22%3EThe%20Israel-Palestine%20War%20Is%20a%20Stain%20on%20Every%20One%20of%20Us%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%2C%20however%2C%20continues%20to%20enjoy%20the%20support%20of%20the%20Western%20powers.%20Through%20various%20wars%20over%20the%20last%20seven%20decades%2C%20it%20has%20extended%20its%20territory%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20today%20it%20occupies%20over%2080%25%20of%20the%20original%20Palestine%20land%20mass.%20The%20Palestinians%20have%20since%20been%20dispossessed%20of%20their%20land%20and%20are%20turned%20into%20refugees.%20Today%201.5%20million%20of%20them%20have%20to%20live%20in%20camps%20with%20poor%20facilities.%20Soon%20after%20the%20establishment%20of%20Israel%20in%201948%2C%20around%2014%20lakh%20Palestinians%20were%20displaced%20from%20which%20emerged%20a%20resistance%20group%20called%20the%20Popular%20Front%20for%20the%20Liberation%20of%20Palestine.%20Leila%20Khalid%20was%20one%20of%20its%20major%20icons.%20The%20other%20major%20figure%20of%20this%20resistance%20was%20Yasser%20Arafat%2C%20who%20took%20the%20middle%20path%20and%20brought%20the%20issue%20to%20the%20global%20forefront.%20The%20Oslo%20Accord%20was%20one%20such%20aborted%20attempt.%20The%20solution%20put%20forth%20by%20the%20global%20community%20%E2%80%93%20a%20two-state%20solution%2C%20with%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%20as%20independent%20nations%20%E2%80%93%20is%20not%20acceptable%20to%20Israel%2C%20for%20it%20does%20not%20recognise%20Palestine.%20Golda%20Meir%2C%20a%20former%20prime%20minister%20of%20Israel%2C%20once%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20is%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20Palestinians%E2%80%9D.%20This%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20is%20the%20underlying%20policy%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20expansion%20of%20Israel%20into%20Palestinian%20territories%20has%20been%20an%20ongoing%20thing%20since%201948%20and%20many%20resolutions%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20have%20not%20been%20followed%20by%20Israel%2C%20as%20America%20stands%20in%20support%20of%20the%20Zionist%20policies%20of%20Israel.%20Israel%2C%20for%20its%20part%2C%20also%20acts%20as%20a%20collaborator%20in%20the%20American%20designs%20to%20control%20oil%20resources%20in%20the%20region.%20The%20UN%2C%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Funispal%2Fdocument%2Fauto-insert-180327%2F%5C%22%3EResolution%203379%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201975%2C%20stated%20that%20Zionism%20is%20a%20form%20of%20racism%20and%20racial%20discrimination.%20However%2C%20later%20another%20resolution%20rolled%20back%20the%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPalestinians%20are%20probably%20the%20worst%20ever%20sufferers%20of%20discrimination%20and%20are%20being%20exiled%20from%20their%20own%20land.%20This%20is%2C%20perhaps%2C%20the%20most%20cruel%20outcome%20of%20British%20colonialism%20and%20the%20United%20States%E2%80%99%20imperial%20designs.%20With%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20influence%20waning%20over%20the%20last%20few%20decades%2C%20the%20question%20that%20arises%20is%20who%20will%20do%20justice%20to%20the%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20with%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20latest%20attack%2C%20the%20gross%20injustice%20against%20Palestinians%20by%20Israel%20has%20intensified%2C%20as%20the%20West%20continues%20to%20support%20Israel.%20However%2C%20peace%20will%20remain%20elusive%20in%20the%20region%20without%20addressing%20the%20root%20of%20the%20problem%2C%20which%20is%20the%20Zionist%20expansionism%20and%20suppression%20of%20the%20Palestinians.%20For%20lasting%20solution%20and%20peace%20in%20West%20Asia%2C%20underlying%20issues%20of%20conflict%20need%20to%20be%20addressed.%20One%20silver%20lining%20following%20the%20latest%20conflict%20is%20that%20a%20number%20of%20Jews%20around%20the%20world%20have%20been%20protesting%20against%20the%20high-handedness%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fram-puniyani%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERam%20Puniyani%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20president%20of%20the%20Centre%20of%20Study%20of%20Society%20and%20Secularism%20and%20has%20written%20several%20books%20including%20%3C%2Fem%3ECommunal%20Politics%3A%20Facts%20Versus%20Myths%3Cem%3E%C2%A0(Sage%2C%202003)%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EDeconstructing%20Terrorist%20Violence%3Cem%3E%C2%A0(Sage%202015)%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EIndian%20Nationalism%20versus%20Hindu%20Nationalism%3Cem%3E%C2%A0(Pharos%202014)%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eand%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3ECaste%20and%20Communalism%3Cem%3E%C2%A0(Olive%202013).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698381010000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26153147%2F1200px-Flickr_-_Government_Press_Office_GPO_-_Arab_People_fleeing.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fby-fully-supporting-israel-the-west-has-chosen-to-forget-the-suffering-of-palestinians%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20aftermath%20of%20Hamas's%20attack%2C%20the%20West%20has%20fully%20thrown%20its%20weight%20behind%20Israel.%20Such%20an%20approach%2C%20however%2C%20takes%20the%20world%20further%20away%20from%20addressing%20the%20root%20cause%20of%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fby-fully-supporting-israel-the-west-has-chosen-to-forget-the-suffering-of-palestinians%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israel-Hamas%20war%3A%20Arab%20nations%20condemn%2C%20reject%20acts%20of%20violence%2C%20terrorism%20against%20civilians%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698380671000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104743333%2Ci