n%20Thursday%20(October%2026)%20extended%20the%20internet%20shutdown%20in%20the%20state%20for%20another%20five%20days%2C%20until%20October%2031.%20This%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20chief%20minister%20N.%20Biren%20Singh%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fmanipur-cm-n-biren-singh-assures-restoration-of-mobile-internet-soon-11697641275116.html%5C%22%3Ehad%20said%20on%20October%2018%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20internet%20would%20be%20restored%20in%20the%20state%20within%20four%20or%20five%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20notification%20on%20the%20extension%20was%20similar%20to%20notifications%20that%20have%20been%20issued%20ever%20since%20ethnic%20violence%20began%20on%20May%203.%20There%20are%20%E2%80%9Capprehensions%20that%20some%20anti-social%20elements%20might%20use%20social%20media%20extensively%20for%20transmission%20of%20images%2C%20hate%20speech%20and%20hate%20videos%20inciting%20the%20passions%20of%20the%20public%20which%20might%20have%20serious%20repercussions%20on%20the%20law%20and%20order%20situation%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fnorth-east%2Fmobile-internet-ban-in-manipur-extended-till-oct-31-govt-order%2Fcid%2F1975561%5C%22%3EPTI%20quoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20Thursday%E2%80%99s%20notification%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECommissioner%20(home)%20T.%20Ranjit%20Singh%20had%20reportedly%20told%20the%20DGP%20in%20letter%20dated%20October%20%E2%80%9Cthat%20there%20are%20still%20reports%20of%20incidents%20of%20violence%20like%20confrontation%20of%20the%20public%20with%20security%20forces%2C%20attempts%20to%20mob%20elected%20members%20residences%20and%20civil%20protests%20in%20front%20of%20police%20stations.%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CTo%20thwart%20the%20designs%20and%20activities%20of%20anti-nationals%20and%20anti-socials%20and%20to%20maintain%20peace%20and%20communal%20harmony%20and%20to%20prevent%20any%20loss%20of%20life%2C%20it%20has%20become%20necessary%20to%20take%20adequate%20measures